"comments": 2, "created_at": "2023-01-22T15:23:55Z", "updated_at": "2023-01-26T09:14:05Z", "closed_at": "2023-01-26T09:14:05Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "### Code\n\n```Rust\nstruct Foo;\n// const A_CONST: usize = 1;\nimpl Foo {\n    const A_CONST: usize = 1;\n    fn foo() -> usize {\n        // const A_CONST: usize = 1;\n        A_CONST\n    }\n}\n```\n\n\n### Current output\n\n```Shell\nerror[E0425]: cannot find value `A_CONST` in this scope\n --> src/lib.rs:7:9\n  |\n7 |         A_CONST\n  |         ^^^^^^^ not found in this scope\n```\n\n\n### Desired output\n\n```Shell\nhelp: try referring to the associated constant: `Self::A_CONST`\n```\n\n\n### Rationale and extra context\n\nAssociated constants work entirely differently from constants at a higher scope (module) or lower (function) which are looked up lexically \u2014 if either of the other two declarations in the sample code are uncommented, compilation succeeds. This may be surprising to beginners ([example that inspired this post](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/75199496/why-cant-you-put-constants-in-an-impl-block)), and the \u201cwhat they meant\u201d is fairly obvious, so this should be a good opportunity to help in the error message.\n\nAdditionally, if the suggestion is machine-applicable then it can be used to help refactor code when a constant was intentionally converted into an associated constant.\n\n### Other cases\n\n_No response_\n\n### Anything else?\n\n_No response_\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_START -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_START -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_DATA_START$${\"user\":\"euclio\"}$$TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_DATA_END -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_END -->\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_END -->", "closed_by": {"login": "bors", "id": 3372342, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMzNzIzNDI=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3372342?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors", "html_url": "https://github.com/bors", "followers_url": "htt